Selecting the right retinol involves balancing potency with your skin's tolerance level. The following products are top-rated for targeting dark spots and uneven skin tone.

== Best for Beginners & Sensitive Skin

=== CeraVe Resurfacing Retinol Serum
- *Key Ingredients:* Encapsulated Retinol, Niacinamide, Licorice Root, Ceramides.
- *Why it works:* Gentle slow-release formula that calms the skin while fading dark spots.
- *Best for:* Budget-conscious users and those prone to irritation.

=== Kiehl's Micro-Dose Anti-Aging Retinol Serum
- *Key Ingredients:* Pure Retinol, Ceramides, Peptides.
- *Why it works:* Formulated to minimize redness and peeling.
- *Best for:* Dry skin and first-time retinol users.

=== La Roche-Posay Retinol B3 Serum
- *Key Ingredients:* Pure Retinol + Gradual Release Retinol, Vitamin B3 (Niacinamide).
- *Why it works:* Lightweight and hydrating; targets fine lines and dark spots simultaneously.

== Best for Experienced Users (Hardcore)

=== Paula's Choice CLINICAL 1% Retinol Treatment
- *Key Ingredients:* 1% Retinol, Vitamin C, Peptides.
- *Why it works:* High concentration for stubborn melasma and sun damage. 
- *Note:* Use a slow-release delivery system, but high potency requires a "sandwich" method for some.

=== The Inkey List SuperSolutions 1% Retinol Serum
- *Key Ingredients:* 1% Retinol, Apricot Kernel Oil, Squalane.
- *Why it works:* Intense formula at a very affordable price point.

=== SkinCeuticals Retinol 1.0
- *Key Ingredients:* 1% Pure Retinol, Bisabolol (calming).
- *Why it works:* Maximum strength OTC concentration. 
- *Best for:* Significant photo-aging and age spots.

